When a student account is created, it automatically links to an assigned Educator account. The Educator gains view-only access to the student’s activity within the app, including:

The prompts the student has submitted.

The responses generated.

The student’s interaction history (e.g. edits, retries, refinements).

Educators cannot send messages through this interface, nor can students contact educators directly within the app. The purpose is solely observational — to allow educators to:

Track how students are engaging with the tool.

Monitor patterns of thinking, problem-solving, and reflection.

Support student learning by reviewing evidence of their approach.

This feature ensures accountability and transparency, while maintaining a clear boundary between student and educator communication.

Multi-Educator Student Access

 Each student has a single account.

 Multiple educators can be granted access to one or more students. To support a shared education environment.

Changes made by any educator are reflected in real-time across all users with access.